00:15:39,750 --> 00:15:42,260
Nagisa's the one coming up with the plot again.

269
00:15:42,260 --> 00:15:45,750
Sounds like she's hit a wall,
so would you give her some advice?

270
00:15:45,750 --> 00:15:48,490
We'll go look for Sanae-san.

271
00:15:48,490 --> 00:15:49,800
You got it.

272
00:15:52,420 --> 00:15:55,470
They weren't meeting here?

273
00:15:55,470 --> 00:15:58,030
I didn't hear anything.

274
00:15:58,030 --> 00:16:00,600
I was planning on following Sanae-san.

275
00:16:01,530 --> 00:16:04,970
Well, I'm sure we can leave Sanae-san alone.

276
00:16:05,560 --> 00:16:07,770
How about we go hang out somewhere, too?

277
00:16:09,270 --> 00:16:12,650
If you only worry about Sunohara, it'll tire you out, right?

278
00:16:20,170 --> 00:16:21,970
It's so cute!

279
00:16:21,970 --> 00:16:23,650
It'll probably look good on you.

280
00:16:23,650 --> 00:16:27,300
I wish you were really my brother.

281
00:16:27,300 --> 00:16:29,300
Do you really mean that?

282
00:16:29,300 --> 00:16:30,670
I do.

283
00:16:30,670 --> 00:16:33,230
Then try treating me like I'm your brother.

284
00:16:33,230 --> 00:16:34,920
Like you're my brother?

285
00:16:35,260 --> 00:16:36,300
Then...

286
00:16:36,300 --> 00:16:38,010
Hey, Onii-chan.

287
00:16:39,230 --> 00:16:40,860
What's wrong, Onii-chan?

288
00:16:40,860 --> 00:16:42,010
N-Nothing.

289
00:16:42,540 --> 00:16:44,460
That was more effective than I'd thought.

290
00:16:44,460 --> 00:16:47,480
What are you saying?
You're so weird, Onii-chan.

291
00:16:47,980 --> 00:16:49,740
This is dangerous.

292
00:16:50,780 --> 00:16:53,380
No more "Onii-chan"!

293
00:16:53,380 --> 00:16:57,330
Why? I can't call you "Onii-chan", Onii-chan?

294
00:16:57,330 --> 00:16:59,700
Actually, don't stop.

295
00:17:03,960 --> 00:17:05,640
You guys...

296
00:17:05,640 --> 00:17:06,540
Since when?

297
00:17:07,510 --> 00:17:10,460
He's making Mei-chan call him "Onii-chan".

298
00:17:10,460 --> 00:17:11,750
He's dangerous.

299
00:17:11,750 --> 00:17:13,740
He looked really turned on.

300
00:17:13,740 --> 00:17:15,590
Oka... Okazaki-kun...

301
00:17:15,590 --> 00:17:17,670
No. There's a reason behind this.

302
00:17:18,160 --> 00:17:20,170
We didn't see anything.

303
00:17:20,170 --> 00:17:21,260
You'll infect us with your idiocy.

304
00:17:21,260 --> 00:17:22,240
Run for it.

305
00:17:22,240 --> 00:17:23,300
You got it wrong!

306
00:17:23,670 --> 00:17:25,020
Hurry!

307
00:17:24,310 --> 00:17:25,020
Wait...

308
00:17:25,020 --> 00:17:26,430
Don't follow us!

309
00:17:26,890 --> 00:17:28,520
No more "Onii-chan" after all!

310
00:17:29,520 --> 00:17:31,560
Actually, I take that back.

311
00:17:33,360 --> 00:17:36,360
Onii-chan. What should Mei do?

312
00:17:36,360 --> 00:17:38,250
No more!

313
00:17:38,250 --> 00:17:41,180
I forbid it!!!

314
00:17:42,200 --> 00:17:44,700
Wow! There are so many to choose from!

315
00:17:44,700 --> 00:17:47,110
The city is amazing after all.

316
00:17:47,110 --> 00:17:49,380
This isn't really a city, you know.

317
00:17:50,030 --> 00:17:51,220
Want me to treat you?

318
00:17:51,220 --> 00:17:52,550
Really?

319
00:17:52,550 --> 00:17:55,120
Then I'll have...

320
00:17:55,500 --> 00:17:56,720
This one!

321
00:17:56,720 --> 00:17:59,000
I've never seen something like this before!

322
00:17:59,510 --> 00:18:01,290
Princess Crepe?

323
00:18:01,290 --> 00:18:03,140
She's right, I've never seen anything like this before.

324
00:18:03,440 --> 00:18:06,050
Hey, the price is princess-like, too.

325
00:18:06,050 --> 00:18:07,990
Girls are unbelievable.

326
00:18:08,900 --> 00:18:09,980
How about something else?

327
00:18:09,980 --> 00:18:12,360
How about the Maharajah Crepe-

328
00:18:11,660 --> 00:18:12,820
Onii-chan...

329
00:18:12,820 --> 00:18:16,340
Mei wants to eat the Princess Crepe.

330
00:18:19,820 --> 00:18:22,200
It's delicious!

331
00:18:22,750 --> 00:18:23,790
I'm such a...

332
00:18:23,790 --> 00:18:25,580
Do you want to try some, too?

333
00:18:25,580 --> 00:18:27,850
Then I'll take a bite.

334
00:18:32,910 --> 00:18:34,960
You took the strawberry.

335
00:18:34,960 --> 00:18:37,610
You said I can try some.

336
00:18:37,610 --> 00:18:39,550
I hate you, Onii-chan.

337
00:18:39,550 --> 00:18:42,350
No! Don't hate me!

338
00:18:42,350 --> 00:18:44,900
Then can we do that together?

339
00:18:45,810 --> 00:18:47,810
Then I'll forgive you.

340
00:18:47,810 --> 00:18:49,910
You're kidding. That's so lame.

341
00:18:49,910 --> 00:18:52,310
Strawberry!

342
00:18:51,170 --> 00:18:52,310
Okay, okay!

343
00:18:52,730 --> 00:18:54,320
Maybe it's this?

344
00:18:54,820 --> 00:18:55,780
This?

345
00:18:56,600 --> 00:18:58,150
This is so exciting.

346
00:18:58,150 --> 00:19:00,030
Choose a frame you like.

347
00:19:00,030 --> 00:19:01,010
Which one do you want?

348
00:19:02,360 --> 00:19:03,670
This one!

349
00:19:03,670 --> 00:19:04,540
Okay.

350
00:19:05,580 --> 00:19:07,790
We'll now take the picture.

351
00:19:07,790 --> 00:19:08,290
Okay!

352
00:19:08,290 --> 00:19:09,420
Ready?

353
00:19:09,790 --> 00:19:11,540
Say "Cheese!"

354
00:19:18,400 --> 00:19:20,340
This is really embarrassing, you know?

355
00:19:19,520 --> 00:19:23,070
Okazaki-san! Make sure you put it on your student ID!

356
00:19:22,390 --> 00:19:24,000
No way!

357
00:19:31,310 --> 00:19:32,370
Hey.

358
00:19:33,560 --> 00:19:35,990
Where've you been?

359
00:19:35,990 --> 00:19:37,700
I was meeting my girlfriend.

360
00:19:37,700 --> 00:19:39,570
What were you two doing?

361
00:19:39,570 --> 00:19:41,490
We were looking for-

362
00:19:41,490 --> 00:19:42,600
What's this?

363
00:19:46,070 --> 00:19:47,490
What's the meaning of this?

364
00:19:47,490 --> 00:19:49,800
It's none of your business!

365
00:19:49,800 --> 00:19:51,110
Give it back to me!

366
00:19:51,110 --> 00:19:54,000
Man, looks like the truth has come out.

367
00:19:54,960 --> 00:19:57,160
It's just as you imagined.

368
00:19:57,160 --> 00:19:59,960
Mei-chan's boyfriend turns out to be me.

369
00:20:00,450 --> 00:20:02,720
What happened to Nagisa-chan?

370
00:20:02,720 --> 00:20:05,050
Obviously, I'm breaking up with her.

371
00:20:05,050 --> 00:20:08,990
The truth is, Mei-chan actually stayed over at my place last night, too.

372
00:20:09,390 --> 00:20:10,390
Right, Mei?

373
00:20:10,390 --> 00:20:14,980
Y-Yeah. I was alone with Okazaki-san, too.

374
00:20:18,360 --> 00:20:20,990
Shall we get a move on, Mei?

375
00:20:20,990 --> 00:20:21,830
Yes.

376
00:20:24,510 --> 00:20:25,200
Wait...

377
00:20:28,440 --> 00:20:29,420
I said wait...

378
00:20:41,840 --> 00:20:43,840
Why does it have to turn out like that?

379
00:20:47,410 --> 00:20:48,350
Damn it!

380
00:21:08,400 --> 00:21:11,040
And nothing more?

381
00:21:11,040 --> 00:21:14,380
I tried to pull off an act thinking we'd make him worry.

382
00:21:14,380 --> 00:21:17,260
I'm sorry, all for our sake...

383
00:21:17,260 --> 00:21:18,070
It's all right.

384
00:21:18,450 --> 00:21:22,640
But even with all the provocation, he didn't say anything.

385
00:21:23,550 --> 00:21:27,330
I was hoping he'd show his "reliable brother" side.

386
00:21:29,050 --> 00:21:33,130
It looks like he doesn't care about me.

387
00:21:33,130 --> 00:21:35,160
That can't be true!

388
00:21:35,600 --> 00:21:38,390
But, lying is wrong.

389
00:21:39,100 --> 00:21:42,350
Mei-chan, shouldn't you go home soon?

390
00:21:42,350 --> 00:21:44,080
You've been absent from school a whole week.

391
00:21:44,080 --> 00:21:46,250
Your parents must be worried about you, too.

392
00:21:46,250 --> 00:21:48,290
I can't go home leaving things the way they are.

393
00:21:48,290 --> 00:21:50,650
Not until Onii-chan gets his act together.

394
00:21:52,070 --> 00:21:53,040
Okazaki-san.

395
00:21:53,040 --> 00:21:57,500
I want Onii-chan to play soccer again.

396
00:21:57,500 --> 00:22:02,300
If he plays soccer again, maybe he'll return to the way he used to be.

397
00:22:02,880 --> 00:22:05,260
If possible, he should return to the Soccer Team and...

398
00:22:05,730 --> 00:22:07,320
I think that's difficult.

399
00:22:07,320 --> 00:22:11,930
You know what happened between Sunohara and the Soccer Team, right?

400
00:22:12,630 --> 00:22:16,110
But I think that's our only chance.

401
00:23:50,590 --> 00:23:53,080
I'm busy taking care of matters with Sanae-san.

402
00:23:53,080 --> 00:23:55,310
I don't have time to worry about Mei.

403
00:23:56,100 --> 00:23:58,620
Mei-chan, let's think it through.

404
00:24:00,750 --> 00:24:06,210
He has alot of good traits
but just can't express them well.

405
00:24:17,620 --> 00:24:19,470
You wanna fight, Okazaki?
